	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St. Thomas</placeName> <date>10<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Feb. 1862</date>.</p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir.</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">I have been requested to forward you<lb/> the bridal cards which I have the pleasure of enclosing here&#8222;<lb/>with.  The nuptials of my sister were celebrated last week.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">There has lately appeared in our paper an un&#8222;<lb/>warranted and unbecoming attack on <persName>Mr. Myers</persName> on account<lb/> of his friends&#39; using the title of &#8220;Rev. Dr.&#8221; before his name.  The<lb/> Representatives of our congregation immediately deemed it their<lb/> duty to speak in <persName>Mr. Myers&#39;</persName> vindication.  According to an article<lb/> in the Chronicle the title Morenu Rab means Dr. of the Law&#59; can<lb/> therefore that of Dr. be used with all correctness&#63;  And&#44; by the way&#44;<lb/> as you have seen <persName>Mr. Myers&#39;</persName> writings&#44; I would&#44; if you do not consid&#8222;<lb/>er improper&#44; ask your opinion of their merits.</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)">I am&#44; Rev. Sir&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)">Truly yours&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">David M. Pizal</persName></p>
			
